<subSubSection id="C3266529FFB6FFA3FF0CFF38DD03FF7D" pageId="8" pageNumber="333" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFB6FFA3FF0CFF38DD03FF7D" blockId="8.[151,1437,150,465]" pageId="8" pageNumber="333">
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFB6FFA3FF0CFF38D903FF35" bold="true" box="[199,322,150,176]" pageId="8" pageNumber="333">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Length 
<quantity id="4CC49B47FFB6FFA3FE54FF38DA68FF34" box="[415,553,150,177]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" metricValueMax="1.7" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="8" pageNumber="333" unit="mm" value="1.6" valueMax="1.7" valueMin="1.5">1.5–1.7 mm</quantity>
; female frons flat, smooth, shiny, with scant setae; scapus triangular to slightly falcate, with small dorsal tuft of setae; eyes separated above by 2.5–2.7 × their width; pronotal and elytral disc smooth and shiny; interstriae with rows of erect and narrowly spatulate setae mainly restricted to declivity.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3266529FFB6FFA3FF0CFEACDA7CFE0C" pageId="8" pageNumber="333" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFB6FFA3FF0CFEACDB7FFEC5" blockId="8.[151,1437,150,465]" pageId="8" pageNumber="333">
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFB6FFA3FF0CFEACD9B2FE99" bold="true" box="[199,499,258,284]" pageId="8" pageNumber="333">Distribution and biology.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="F32B7632FFB6FFA3FE31FEACDAC2FE99" box="[506,643,258,284]" name="Madagascar" pageId="8" pageNumber="333">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
. Breeds under bark of very dry 
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D21FFB6FFA3FC21FEADDC39FE98" box="[1002,1144,259,285]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Cryptocarya" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="8" pageNumber="333" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFB6FFA3FC21FEADDC39FE98" box="[1002,1144,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="333">Cryptocarya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
branches. One brood was recorded, consisting of 
<specimenCount id="9D3AFD2BFFB6FFA3FE55FE89DA69FEC4" box="[414,552,295,321]" pageId="8" pageNumber="333" type="pupa">seven pupae</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount id="9D3AFD2BFFB6FFA3FD95FE89DA87FEC5" box="[606,710,294,321]" pageId="8" pageNumber="333" type="adult">one adult</specimenCount>
specimen.
</paragraph>
